# ── StayInsight AI – Frontend Environment Variables ───────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env` (same folder) for local overrides — Vite only
# ever reads variables prefixed with VITE_, and only at build time.
#
# In local dev you normally do NOT need this file: vite.config.js already
# proxies '/api' to http://localhost:5000, so the frontend and backend
# behave as if they were on the same origin.
#
# In production the frontend (e.g. Vercel) and backend (e.g. Render) are
# deployed to two different origins, so the frontend needs to be told the
# full URL of the deployed backend's API.

# VITE_API_URL: absolute base URL of the deployed backend API, INCLUDING
# the /api suffix. Leave unset for local dev (falls back to '/api', which
# the Vite dev server proxies to localhost:5000).
#
# Example (Render backend):
VITE_API_URL="https://your-backend-service.onrender.com/api"
